# Fluff Date: 2026-02-16 11:04:06
overview:<p>The Stag emerged from Clan Wolverine's ambitious military expansion program following Operation Klondike. Blessed with an abundance of captured Vulcan BattleMechs, Khan Sarah McEvedy recognized that mere duplication of Inner Sphere designs would never fulfill the Wolverines' future strategic requirements. She ordered a comprehensive redesign that transformed the venerable infantry-killer into a high-speed cavalry platform capable of both reconnaissance and direct engagement.</p><p>Introduced in 2823, the Stag represented a dramatic philosophical departure from its progenitor. Where the Vulcan excelled at infantry suppression, the Stag was purpose-built for rapid strikes against 'Mech-scale targets, utilizing Star League-era technologies including an Endo Steel frame, XL engine, and double heat sinks. The deviation was so substantial that Clan engineers considered it an entirely new design rather than a standard IIC-style rebuild.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Stag retains the Vulcan's top speed of 97 kilometers per hour while adding MASC capability that enables bursts up to 130 kilometers per hour, allowing pilots to rapidly close with targets or disengage from unfavorable engagements. This speed comes at the cost of the original's jump capability, trading vertical mobility for raw ground speed. Ten tons of armor provide maximum protection for the forty-five ton chassis, a significant improvement over the lightly-armored Vulcan.</p><p>Weaponry centers on an ER Large Laser for long-range engagements, supported by paired medium lasers and SRM-4 launchers for close-quarters combat. Two tons of CASE-protected missile ammunition grant MechWarriors flexibility to employ specialized munitions against varied targets. An active probe enhances the 'Mech's reconnaissance capability, allowing it to detect hidden units and feed targeting data to friendly forces. Twelve double heat sinks efficiently manage the thermal load from sustained laser fire.</p><p>The Stag's improved communications and sensor systems reflect its dual role as both striker and scout, while a stabilized weapon mount on the right arm ER Large Laser ensures accurate fire even during high-speed maneuvers. However, the design carries a troubled legacy—its association with the annihilated Wolverines means any surviving examples draw immediate hostility from Clan warriors who recognize the chassis.</p>

deployment:<p>The Stag II emerged as an enhanced combat variant during Clan Wolverine's final desperate months. Engineers replaced the MASC system with a more powerful engine achieving 119 kilometers per hour sustained speed, while mounting a prototype Extended Range PPC in place of the ER Large Laser. The SRM systems gave way to an expanded laser array comprising three medium lasers, two medium pulse lasers, and two small lasers, eliminating ammunition dependency for improved field endurance. Ferro-fibrous armor compensated partially for protection reductions necessitated by these modifications. It remains unclear whether any Stag II units survived the Trial of Annihilation, though at least one example reportedly saw combat straight from the factory during the Wolverines' last stand.</p>

history:<p>The Stag's operational history proved tragically brief. First Stags were rushed directly from factory lines into combat as Clan Wolverine's relations with neighboring Clans deteriorated catastrophically in 2823. The design saw significant action during the Wolverines' desperate war against the combined might of the other Clans, its speed and firepower proving valuable in the running battles that characterized that conflict.</p><p>The Stag II variant emerged during this same period, representing an attempt to further enhance the design's combat effectiveness. Engineers sacrificed the MASC system for a more powerful engine capable of 119 kilometers per hour sustained speed, while replacing the ER Large Laser with a prototype Extended Range PPC. The missile systems gave way to an expanded laser array—three medium lasers, two medium pulse lasers, and two small lasers—dramatically improving field endurance by eliminating ammunition dependency. Ferro-fibrous armor partially offset the protection lost to accommodate these changes.</p><p>Following the Trial of Annihilation that destroyed Clan Wolverine, surviving Stags were claimed as isorla by the victorious Clans. Most were likely dismantled after study, their tainted association with the "Not-Named Clan" making continued service politically impossible. Whether any examples survived the Wolverines' destruction remains unclear, though the design's specifications were preserved in Clan records and eventually surfaced in intelligence documents recovered during the Jihad.</p><p>The Stag carries the "Bad Reputation (Clan)" quirk in recognition of this dark history—any Clan warrior encountering the design would immediately recognize its Wolverine origins and react with the visceral hostility reserved for all things associated with the annihilated Clan.</p>

